The paper deals with information theoretic measures and their application in a communication channel with a confidential message. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the security of the communication channel, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions interference channels, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses coding schemes, which could place it in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
